name: r-kableextra
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.3.4" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-kableextra
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/kableExtra_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/kableExtra/kableExtra_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 091ffac282cf9257edcec1a06da38b5e6516f111296bedb934e32f5692ffbbb0

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-digest
    - r-glue
    - r-htmltools
    - r-knitr >=1.16
    - r-magrittr
    - r-rmarkdown >=1.6.0
    - r-rstudioapi
    - r-rvest
    - r-scales
    - r-stringr >=1.0
    - r-svglite
    - r-viridislite
    - r-webshot
    - r-xml2 >=1.1.1
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-digest
    - r-glue
    - r-htmltools
    - r-knitr >=1.16
    - r-magrittr
    - r-rmarkdown >=1.6.0
    - r-rstudioapi
    - r-rvest
    - r-scales
    - r-stringr >=1.0
    - r-svglite
    - r-viridislite
    - r-webshot
    - r-xml2 >=1.1.1

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('kableExtra')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('kableExtra')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://haozhu233.github.io/kableExtra/, https://github.com/haozhu233/kableExtra
  license: MIT
  summary: "Build complex HTML or 'LaTeX' tables using 'kable()' from 'knitr'  and the piping syntax from 'magrittr'. Function 'kable()' is a light weight  table generator coming from 'knitr'. This package simplifies the way to  manipulate the HTML or 'LaTeX' codes generated by 'kable()' and allows  users to construct complex\
    \ tables and customize styles using a readable  syntax. "
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - PertuyF
